A '''notice of default''' is a notification given to a [[borrower]] stating that he or she has not made their [[payment]]s by the predetermined deadline, or is otherwise in default on the mortgage contract. Other ways a borrower may be in default include not providing proper insurance coverage for the property, or not paying due property taxes as agreed. It dictates that if the money owed (plus an additional [[legal fee]]), or other breach(es) are not paid/remedied in a given time, the [[lender]] may choose to [[foreclose]] the borrower's property. Any other people who may be affected by the [[foreclosure]] may also receive a copy of the notification.

